Package: matchatr
Title: Causal Inference for Case-Control, Nested Case-Control, and
    Case-Cohort Studies
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R:
    person("Lorenzo", "Fabbri", , "lorenzo.fabbri92sm@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0003-3031-322X"))
Description: Classical and causal estimation for (matched) case-control,
    nested case-control, and case-cohort study designs. Provides
    conditional logistic regression and risk-set-sampled / weighted Cox
    models for design-faithful odds-ratio and hazard-ratio estimation,
    plus marginal causal effects via case-control weighting (the Rose and
    van der Laan g-formula, inverse-probability weighting, augmented IPW,
    and targeted maximum likelihood family) and design-based inclusion
    weighting (Samuelsen and Borgan). Integrates with the etverse engine
    (causatr for g-computation / IPW / AIPW with sandwich and bootstrap
    variance, survatr for causal survival on person-period data) so that
    case-control and design weights compose directly with existing
    estimators. Part of the etverse ecosystem.
